### HYMN XCVIII

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2009801">1</span></span>That we may
win us wealth and spoil we poets verily call on  
   thee.  
  In war men call on thee, Indra, the hero's Lord, in the steed's,  
   race-course call on thee.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_2009802">2</span></span>As such, O
Wonderful whose hand holds thunder, praised as  
   mighty, Caster of the Stone.  
  Pour on us boldly, Indra, kie and chariot-steeds, ever to be the  
   conqueror's strength.

